    "",
    "**d)** First: (x cos x - sin x)/x², Second: quotient rule on this",
    "",
    "**e)** First: [(2x)(x+1) - x²(1)]/(x+1)² = (x² + 2x)/(x+1)², Second: quotient rule again",
    "",
    "### Exercise 14: Applications of Differentiation Rules",
    "",
    "**a)** y = x² sin x, y' = 2x sin x + x² cos x, at x = π/2: 2(π/2) sin(π/2) + (π/2)² cos(π/2) = π × 1 + (π²/4) × 0 = π, tangent: y - (π/2)² sin(π/2) = π (x - π/2), y - (π²/4) × 1 = π (x - π/2)",
